{"id":898803508,"lang":"cpp","lang_name":"C++","time":"6 months, 4 weeks","timestamp":1676505109,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"11 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/898803508/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Roman to Integer","memory":"6.1 MB","code":"class Solution {\npublic:\n    int num(char c) {\n        int res = 0;\n        if (c == 'I') res = 1;\n        if (c == 'V') res = 5;\n        if (c == 'X') res = 10;\n        if (c == 'L') res = 50;\n        if (c == 'C') res = 100;\n        if (c == 'D') res = 500;\n        if (c == 'M') res = 1000;\n        return res;\n    }\n    int romanToInt(string s) {\n        int res = 0;\n        for (int i = 0; i < s.size(); i++){\n            bool s1 = (s[i] == 'I' && (s[i + 1] == 'V' || s[i + 1] == 'X'));\n            bool s2 = (s[i] == 'X' && (s[i + 1] == 'L' || s[i + 1] == 'C'));\n            bool s3 = (s[i] == 'C' && (s[i + 1] == 'D' || s[i + 1] == 'M'));\n            if ((s1 || s2 || s3) && i != (s.size() - 1)) {\n                res += (num(s[i+1]) - num(s[i]));\n                i++;\n            }\n            else res += num(s[i]);\n        }\n        return res;\n    }\n};","compare_result":"","title_slug":"roman-to-integer","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
